1
00:00:31,573 --> 00:00:35,953
BEYOND THE BAR

2
00:00:37,037 --> 00:00:40,040
FRUITS & VEGETABLES

3
00:03:34,881 --> 00:03:36,299
Kang Hyo-min speaking.

4
00:03:36,842 --> 00:03:38,719
<i>Ms. Kang Hyo-min?</i>

5
00:03:38,802 --> 00:03:39,678
Yes.

6
00:03:40,303 --> 00:03:43,724
This is Detective Han Su-cheol
from the Jicheong Violent Crimes Unit.

7
00:03:44,474 --> 00:03:45,684
What can I do for you?

8
00:03:45,767 --> 00:03:48,854
Ms. Kim Yeong-mi was arrested today
on suspicion of murder.

9
00:03:48,937 --> 00:03:50,230
During questioning,

10
00:03:50,731 --> 00:03:53,358
she said you were her attorney,
so I'm contacting you.

11
00:03:53,984 --> 00:03:55,861
- Kim Yeong-mi?
<i>- Yes.</i>

12
00:03:55,944 --> 00:03:59,364
Do you have any personal connection
to Ms. Kim Yeong-mi,

13
00:03:59,448 --> 00:04:01,700
<i>or have you represented her in the past?</i>

14
00:04:01,783 --> 00:04:02,743
No.

15
00:04:02,826 --> 00:04:04,786
I don't think I know her.

16
00:04:05,537 --> 00:04:09,291
She's refused to cooperate
without legal counsel.

17
00:04:10,167 --> 00:04:11,501
You must be busy,

18
00:04:11,585 --> 00:04:14,421
but can you come to the station
to confirm this in person?

19
00:04:14,504 --> 00:04:15,380
Okay.

20
00:04:16,465 --> 00:04:17,674
I will.

21
00:04:29,895 --> 00:04:31,104
Ms. Kim Yeong-mi.

22
00:04:32,773 --> 00:04:34,524
Ms. Kang Hyo-min is here.

23
00:04:35,442 --> 00:04:36,485
You came.

24
00:04:37,277 --> 00:04:38,737
Why don't you two talk?

25
00:04:51,166 --> 00:04:52,334
Have we

26
00:04:53,418 --> 00:04:55,879
met before?

27
00:04:58,215 --> 00:04:59,841
I knew you wouldn't remember me.

28
00:05:00,550 --> 00:05:01,760
Sorry?

29
00:05:02,803 --> 00:05:05,263
You're partly responsible
for what happened to me.

30
00:05:06,431 --> 00:05:07,474
That's why

31
00:05:08,725 --> 00:05:10,185
I'm asking you to represent me.

32
00:05:18,232 --> 00:05:22,739
BYSTANDER

33
00:05:23,782 --> 00:05:24,950
Doesn't ring a bell.

34
00:05:26,451 --> 00:05:27,410
Same here.

35
00:05:28,203 --> 00:05:31,456
Yeong-mi is a common name,
so I think I've heard it somewhere.

36
00:05:31,540 --> 00:05:33,542
You met her and still don't remember her?

37
00:05:33,625 --> 00:05:34,501
No.

38
00:05:34,584 --> 00:05:36,002
We know all of your friends.

39
00:05:36,503 --> 00:05:39,172
Then could she be a friend
from high school?

40
00:05:39,256 --> 00:05:40,924
Maybe.

41
00:05:41,007 --> 00:05:43,301
High school was
the only time we weren't together.

42
00:05:43,385 --> 00:05:44,719
I don't think we were friends.

43
00:05:44,803 --> 00:05:47,389
She's older than me
and didn't go to high school.

44
00:05:47,472 --> 00:05:49,599
Maybe you know the victim, then.

45
00:05:49,683 --> 00:05:51,852
I checked that too, but the victim

46
00:05:51,935 --> 00:05:54,479
only graduated from middle school,
and it was different from ours.

47
00:05:54,563 --> 00:05:56,314
Neither of them went to high school?

48
00:05:56,398 --> 00:06:00,485
The victim went to high school in the US.

49
00:06:00,986 --> 00:06:02,946
It seems she moved after middle school.

50
00:06:06,241 --> 00:06:07,492
So, what will you do?

51
00:06:07,576 --> 00:06:08,660
Are you taking the case?

52
00:06:09,619 --> 00:06:11,538
Not taking the case feels wrong,

53
00:06:11,621 --> 00:06:13,915
but saying yes means
I'll deal with a criminal case.

54
00:06:13,999 --> 00:06:17,129
On top of that,
the firm won't approve it as pro bono,

55
00:06:17,210 --> 00:06:18,753
so I'd have to charge a fee.

56
00:06:19,588 --> 00:06:22,257
But there's no way
Ms. Kim Yeong-mi could afford that.

57
00:06:26,094 --> 00:06:27,762
By the way, when can we go in?

58
00:06:27,846 --> 00:06:30,098
Which treatment are you getting today?

59
00:06:30,181 --> 00:06:31,182
The one she got.

60
00:06:32,517 --> 00:06:33,894
It's really good.

61
00:06:37,105 --> 00:06:38,732
Ms. Kang Hyo-min.

62
00:06:40,609 --> 00:06:41,610
See you.

63
00:06:50,243 --> 00:06:52,329
Does it hurt a lot?

64
00:06:52,412 --> 00:06:53,538
No.

65
00:06:53,622 --> 00:06:55,123
You can relax.

66
00:06:55,206 --> 00:06:56,124
All right.

67
00:06:56,207 --> 00:06:58,126
- I'll get started.
- Okay.

68
00:07:05,967 --> 00:07:08,470
Look how plump her skin looks.

69
00:07:08,553 --> 00:07:10,597
Right? It works really well.

70
00:07:11,222 --> 00:07:12,182
I should get it too.

71
00:07:12,265 --> 00:07:14,476
Do we get a group discount
if we all get it?

72
00:07:14,559 --> 00:07:15,685
I'm not sure.

73
00:07:15,769 --> 00:07:17,020
Ask them when you go.

74
00:07:17,103 --> 00:07:18,939
Let's go together. All three of us.

75
00:07:19,022 --> 00:07:20,357
Okay.

76
00:07:20,857 --> 00:07:21,900
Yeong-mi Kim.

77
00:07:26,446 --> 00:07:29,407
Yeong-mi Kim… Kim Yeong-mi.

78
00:07:33,119 --> 00:07:34,913
KIM YEONG-MI
SANGRIM HIGH, HANMUN MIDDLE SCHOOL

79
00:08:00,355 --> 00:08:01,648
You're smiling again.

80
00:08:17,956 --> 00:08:19,332
That must be Ms. Choi.

81
00:08:41,438 --> 00:08:43,523
The scent's gone already.

82
00:09:11,801 --> 00:09:12,802
Yes.

83
00:09:15,472 --> 00:09:16,723
Good grief.

84
00:09:21,728 --> 00:09:23,229
Good grief.

85
00:09:24,898 --> 00:09:26,149
What's going on?

86
00:09:27,275 --> 00:09:28,902
A lot of things are going on.

87
00:09:30,236 --> 00:09:32,238
What do you think is our team's problem?

88
00:09:36,367 --> 00:09:38,411
I don't think there's
a particular problem.

89
00:09:39,454 --> 00:09:42,290
Our team is way too dry.

90
00:09:42,373 --> 00:09:43,583
We're so dry.

91
00:09:43,666 --> 00:09:47,462
Our team would make a desert
look like an oasis.

92
00:09:49,297 --> 00:09:50,340
Is that so?

93
00:09:53,718 --> 00:09:57,263
Don't you think
we also should be having team dinners?

94
00:09:57,347 --> 00:09:58,848
We just had one a while ago.

95
00:09:58,932 --> 00:10:01,184
Don't tell me
you only want one once a year.

96
00:10:01,267 --> 00:10:04,854
You didn't even join the dinner last time.

97
00:10:05,980 --> 00:10:07,524
Okay, let's have a team dinner.

98
00:10:07,607 --> 00:10:08,775
Yes!

99
00:10:09,776 --> 00:10:11,319
Since we're on the subject,

100
00:10:12,320 --> 00:10:13,863
why not have it today?

101
00:10:13,947 --> 00:10:16,491
If the rest of the team
can make it, why not?

102
00:10:16,574 --> 00:10:18,868
Since team dinners are
an extension of work,

103
00:10:18,952 --> 00:10:21,121
I'll make sure every person attends.

104
00:10:21,204 --> 00:10:22,455
Don't force them, though.

105
00:10:22,539 --> 00:10:25,750
We don't do this often.
Even missing one person kills the vibe.

106
00:10:25,834 --> 00:10:28,002
Especially Ms. Heo Min-jeong,

107
00:10:28,086 --> 00:10:31,089
who didn't attend last time.
I'll make sure she comes today.

108
00:10:36,010 --> 00:10:37,595
Why are you looking at me like that?

109
00:10:39,139 --> 00:10:41,766
I mean, I felt it last time too.

110
00:10:42,350 --> 00:10:45,812
Ms. Heo seems to be a bit less committed

111
00:10:45,895 --> 00:10:49,315
to our team these days.

112
00:10:50,650 --> 00:10:51,609
Though I'm her peer…

113
00:10:52,652 --> 00:10:55,113
I mean, since I'm her peer,

114
00:10:55,196 --> 00:10:58,158
I feel like it's my job
to give her a proper talking-to.

115
00:11:00,535 --> 00:11:01,619
What do you think?

116
00:11:04,664 --> 00:11:06,583
Let me know when the venue is set.

117
00:11:07,333 --> 00:11:08,209
I will.

118
00:11:08,877 --> 00:11:10,128
I'm on it.

119
00:11:11,337 --> 00:11:13,715
She's so dead.

120
00:11:16,467 --> 00:11:18,803
- Here's to a hard day's work!
- To a hard day's work!

121
00:11:18,887 --> 00:11:19,971
Enjoy, everyone.

122
00:11:23,892 --> 00:11:25,518
Glasses up. Come on.

123
00:11:25,602 --> 00:11:28,146
- Back-to-back.
- No breaks.

124
00:11:28,229 --> 00:11:29,772
Cheers!

125
00:11:35,945 --> 00:11:36,863
That's enough.

126
00:11:42,619 --> 00:11:43,745
Eat it with other dishes.

127
00:11:44,412 --> 00:11:46,206
- It melts in your mouth.
- Eat quickly.

128
00:11:46,289 --> 00:11:49,125
- No time to talk. Eat up.
- Eat it.

129
00:11:54,422 --> 00:11:55,632
It's so good.

130
00:12:07,727 --> 00:12:10,188
Alright, then. Shall we do a wave toast?

131
00:12:10,271 --> 00:12:11,147
- Yes!
- Yes!

132
00:12:11,231 --> 00:12:12,190
I love a wave toast.

133
00:12:12,273 --> 00:12:14,359
Let me mix the liquor.

134
00:12:14,442 --> 00:12:15,944
You're no good.

135
00:12:16,027 --> 00:12:17,237
Let me.

136
00:12:17,320 --> 00:12:19,072
Can you mix beer and soju?

137
00:12:19,155 --> 00:12:20,448
I'm an expert.

138
00:12:21,866 --> 00:12:23,117
- Okay.
- Give me the glasses.

139
00:12:23,201 --> 00:12:25,245
Everyone must have been
waiting for tonight.

140
00:12:25,328 --> 00:12:27,080
The ratio of beer and soju is crucial.

141
00:12:27,163 --> 00:12:28,039
Totally. I know.

142
00:12:28,122 --> 00:12:29,874
You're pouring too much soju!

143
00:12:29,958 --> 00:12:31,626
- A bit more.
- How much beer are you pouring?

144
00:12:31,709 --> 00:12:33,878
- Hey, shush!
- Pour just a little less.

145
00:12:33,962 --> 00:12:35,505
Hey!

146
00:12:35,588 --> 00:12:36,965
You said you're an expert.

147
00:12:37,048 --> 00:12:37,924
I'll do it.

148
00:12:47,058 --> 00:12:48,101
What are you up to?

149
00:12:49,644 --> 00:12:52,855
I just needed to get some fresh air.

150
00:12:53,815 --> 00:12:54,941
Are you okay?

151
00:12:55,817 --> 00:12:58,861
Did everything go okay
at the police station the other day?

152
00:13:00,655 --> 00:13:03,074
We've all been too cautious to ask you

153
00:13:03,700 --> 00:13:05,451
about what happened.

154
00:13:08,204 --> 00:13:10,581
I'm still thinking.

155
00:13:12,208 --> 00:13:13,459
What happened?

156
00:13:14,335 --> 00:13:16,546
My mom's always had trouble with men.

157
00:13:18,047 --> 00:13:19,257
She's a smart woman,

158
00:13:19,340 --> 00:13:21,592
but she just doesn't have an eye for men.

159
00:13:22,844 --> 00:13:24,846
When her current boyfriend
heard I was a lawyer,

160
00:13:24,929 --> 00:13:26,723
he talked my mom

161
00:13:26,806 --> 00:13:29,267
into pulling a scam by using my name.

162
00:13:29,851 --> 00:13:32,729
I guess some people still
take a lawyer's word as gospel.

163
00:13:34,105 --> 00:13:36,649
The victim is demanding 20 million won,

164
00:13:36,733 --> 00:13:39,527
saying they'll get my mom
sent to jail if she doesn't pay.

165
00:13:41,070 --> 00:13:44,782
Our entire savings, including the deposit
for our home, is exactly 20 million won.

166
00:13:45,450 --> 00:13:46,826
What a coincidence.

167
00:13:49,287 --> 00:13:53,166
But it's just enough to avoid debt.
Maybe the universe is helping us.

168
00:13:54,125 --> 00:13:56,336
Twenty million won
might not be much to some,

169
00:13:57,128 --> 00:13:59,756
but I spent all of my teens and twenties

170
00:13:59,839 --> 00:14:02,675
working part-time jobs to save that money.

171
00:14:03,593 --> 00:14:07,930
Don't tell me you're planning
to use that money for a settlement.

172
00:14:10,099 --> 00:14:11,434
What else can I do?

173
00:14:12,060 --> 00:14:13,227
If anything,

174
00:14:14,604 --> 00:14:17,440
I think that would be
doing a disservice to your mother.

175
00:14:17,523 --> 00:14:20,276
It could lead to a bigger crime later on.

176
00:14:21,736 --> 00:14:23,780
If a parent jumps into a fire,

177
00:14:23,863 --> 00:14:26,449
does being a good child mean
jumping in after them?

178
00:14:26,532 --> 00:14:28,910
If you take care of this for her,

179
00:14:28,993 --> 00:14:31,788
you might actually take away
her chance for a clean start.

180
00:14:31,871 --> 00:14:35,458
It's better that she learns her lesson now
and starts over.

181
00:14:36,959 --> 00:14:38,211
That's a new perspective.

182
00:14:40,004 --> 00:14:42,840
Thank you. I'll think about it.

183
00:14:53,643 --> 00:14:55,353
Shall we go for round two?

184
00:14:55,436 --> 00:14:56,354
- Yes!
- Yes!

185
00:14:56,437 --> 00:14:58,147
What do you mean, round two?

186
00:14:58,231 --> 00:15:00,650
We keep it simple.
Just dinner with drinks, and that's it.

187
00:15:00,733 --> 00:15:02,860
That's so cold.

188
00:15:04,112 --> 00:15:05,321
Round two crew, assemble!

189
00:15:05,405 --> 00:15:06,614
- Here!
- Here!

190
00:15:07,907 --> 00:15:09,325
I'm drunk. I'll get going.

191
00:15:09,409 --> 00:15:10,451
Thank you.

192
00:15:10,535 --> 00:15:11,494
Come on.

193
00:15:11,577 --> 00:15:14,914
Seriously, she's so heartless.

194
00:15:15,415 --> 00:15:16,582
This is no fun.

195
00:15:17,750 --> 00:15:19,335
- I'm going as well.
- What?

196
00:15:19,419 --> 00:15:21,504
Thank you for the dinner. Bye.

197
00:15:21,587 --> 00:15:23,256
- So heartless.
- I am!

198
00:15:23,339 --> 00:15:24,715
- You're no fun.
- I'm not!

199
00:15:25,258 --> 00:15:27,468
I need to go as well.

200
00:15:28,261 --> 00:15:29,804
Okay. See you tomorrow.

201
00:15:30,763 --> 00:15:32,598
So dry. Too dry.

202
00:15:33,724 --> 00:15:35,393
A word, Ms. Choi?

203
00:15:35,476 --> 00:15:36,394
Sorry?

204
00:15:37,353 --> 00:15:38,563
Okay.

205
00:15:42,942 --> 00:15:45,027
Who's still up for round two?

206
00:15:53,661 --> 00:15:54,787
Here.

207
00:15:54,871 --> 00:15:56,247
What are these?

208
00:15:56,330 --> 00:15:58,583
I bought some clothes for the twins.

209
00:15:58,666 --> 00:16:00,293
Thank you.

210
00:16:00,376 --> 00:16:01,752
Also, the firm offers

211
00:16:01,836 --> 00:16:03,629
housing deposit loans
to eligible associates

212
00:16:03,713 --> 00:16:06,132
at rates lower than the market average.

213
00:16:06,215 --> 00:16:09,177
Once you pass the evaluation
and officially join as an associate,

214
00:16:09,260 --> 00:16:10,887
I'll help you to take advantage of this.

215
00:16:10,970 --> 00:16:12,430
Okay.

216
00:16:12,930 --> 00:16:14,140
With the benefit,

217
00:16:14,223 --> 00:16:18,352
it'd be nice for you to move to a place
where the twins can be more comfortable.

218
00:16:18,936 --> 00:16:21,105
Thank you so much.

219
00:16:26,360 --> 00:16:29,155
But I won't give you a high score
just because you're the breadwinner.

220
00:16:29,238 --> 00:16:31,491
Of course, I understand.

221
00:16:32,408 --> 00:16:33,576
Still,

222
00:16:34,785 --> 00:16:36,704
if you ever need an adult to lean on,

223
00:16:36,787 --> 00:16:39,332
don't go looking elsewhere.
Just come to me.

224
00:16:42,293 --> 00:16:43,252
Okay.

225
00:16:45,171 --> 00:16:46,339
Thank you, Mr. Yoon.

226
00:17:06,734 --> 00:17:08,277
<i>When did I say you could come in?</i>

227
00:17:08,361 --> 00:17:10,029
I'm thirsty, that's all.

228
00:17:10,863 --> 00:17:12,031
Hey!

229
00:17:14,158 --> 00:17:15,409
Shall we have one more beer?

230
00:17:15,493 --> 00:17:16,452
Do you have any?

231
00:17:17,912 --> 00:17:19,455
I'm very drunk

232
00:17:19,539 --> 00:17:20,665
and about to go to bed.

233
00:17:20,748 --> 00:17:22,124
And you're going to leave.

234
00:17:22,208 --> 00:17:23,751
Then get me some water at least.

235
00:17:47,066 --> 00:17:48,025
Listen.

236
00:17:49,402 --> 00:17:51,571
I'm saying this as your close friend.

237
00:17:52,780 --> 00:17:54,156
This woman is off limits.

238
00:17:54,240 --> 00:17:55,366
Why?

239
00:17:55,449 --> 00:17:56,409
I'm older than you--

240
00:17:56,492 --> 00:17:57,577
It doesn't matter.

241
00:17:58,119 --> 00:17:59,078
I've been married.

242
00:18:00,788 --> 00:18:02,498
- I even have a kid.
- She's all grown up.

243
00:18:03,374 --> 00:18:04,375
I can't have a baby.

244
00:18:04,458 --> 00:18:06,252
That's for the gods to decide.

245
00:18:06,794 --> 00:18:08,129
You're overstepping.

246
00:18:08,921 --> 00:18:11,173
- I won't have any more.
- I won't force you to.

247
00:18:12,508 --> 00:18:13,384
What?

248
00:18:14,302 --> 00:18:15,344
What else?

249
00:18:15,886 --> 00:18:18,264
Why am I even having
this conversation with you?

250
00:18:24,979 --> 00:18:25,896
Then let's just date.

251
00:18:28,482 --> 00:18:29,358
Fine.

252
00:18:29,859 --> 00:18:31,527
Let's say I won't get married.

253
00:18:32,153 --> 00:18:33,904
How about you?
Do you have unlimited time?

254
00:18:33,988 --> 00:18:36,073
Doesn't the opportunity cost scare you?

255
00:18:36,157 --> 00:18:38,868
- Don't you plan on getting married?
- I will. I want to.

256
00:18:38,951 --> 00:18:41,245
- With someone I love.
- Exactly.

257
00:18:41,329 --> 00:18:42,872
You're the one I love.

258
00:18:43,706 --> 00:18:45,958
How could I marry someone else
with you around?

259
00:18:53,090 --> 00:18:54,008
You…

260
00:18:57,428 --> 00:18:59,013
I don't deserve you.

261
00:19:01,515 --> 00:19:02,683
You think so?

262
00:19:05,561 --> 00:19:07,521
Then let's do what drunk people do.

263
00:19:08,481 --> 00:19:09,357
What?

264
00:19:10,232 --> 00:19:11,108
Make a mistake.

265
00:19:21,369 --> 00:19:22,453
This is a mistake, okay?

266
00:19:24,080 --> 00:19:24,955
Whatever you say.

267
00:19:51,691 --> 00:19:53,818
<i>X equals negative b, plus or minus.</i>

