00:41:17,308 --> 00:41:19,560
COURT IN SESSION

597
00:41:19,894 --> 00:41:21,813
FIRST CRIMINAL TRIAL HEARING
FOR THE MURDER CHARGE

598
00:41:22,438 --> 00:41:25,149
Counsel, could you repeat that, please?

599
00:41:25,775 --> 00:41:27,902
The defendant pleads not guilty.

600
00:41:27,986 --> 00:41:29,654
What on earth?

601
00:41:29,737 --> 00:41:31,656
How is she not guilty?

602
00:41:31,739 --> 00:41:34,033
My daughter was murdered!

603
00:41:34,117 --> 00:41:36,953
Those in the gallery, please remain quiet.

604
00:41:37,036 --> 00:41:39,247
Sit down.

605
00:41:39,330 --> 00:41:40,206
Counsel,

606
00:41:40,289 --> 00:41:42,500
are you fully aware
that pleading not guilty

607
00:41:42,583 --> 00:41:44,752
to the murder charge

608
00:41:44,836 --> 00:41:47,463
could put the defendant
at a severe disadvantage

609
00:41:47,547 --> 00:41:49,507
in the broader context of this case?

610
00:41:49,590 --> 00:41:52,635
Yes, that has been fully considered.

611
00:41:52,719 --> 00:41:54,637
However, in this case,
the defendant's actions

612
00:41:54,721 --> 00:41:57,849
do not constitute murder under the law.

613
00:41:58,558 --> 00:42:00,518
For a murder charge to be established,

614
00:42:00,601 --> 00:42:03,146
both subjective and objective elements
must be present.

615
00:42:03,229 --> 00:42:04,605
In other words,

616
00:42:04,689 --> 00:42:08,651
the intent to kill and the act of killing
must occur simultaneously.

617
00:42:08,735 --> 00:42:10,611
That was not the case here.

618
00:42:10,695 --> 00:42:12,905
Let me explain with a simple example.

619
00:42:12,989 --> 00:42:16,784
If person A thought about killing person B

620
00:42:16,868 --> 00:42:19,162
but took no action,

621
00:42:19,245 --> 00:42:20,830
it does not constitute murder.

622
00:42:21,456 --> 00:42:23,750
If, on the following day,
person A had a change of heart

623
00:42:23,833 --> 00:42:26,794
and no longer intended to kill person B,

624
00:42:26,878 --> 00:42:30,673
but person B died due to person A
accidentally dropping something,

625
00:42:30,757 --> 00:42:33,342
this too would not constitute murder.

626
00:42:33,426 --> 00:42:34,719
This is because

627
00:42:34,802 --> 00:42:38,556
the intent and the action
did not take place at the same time.

628
00:42:40,016 --> 00:42:42,769
The same applies to the defendant,
Kim Yeong-mi.

629
00:42:42,852 --> 00:42:46,689
<i>The first act,</i>
<i>the blow with a blunt object,</i>

630
00:42:47,315 --> 00:42:51,360
<i>was made with intent to injure,</i>
<i>but it did not lead to the victim's death.</i>

631
00:42:51,444 --> 00:42:52,862
The second act,

632
00:42:52,945 --> 00:42:56,365
<i>the collision which resulted</i>
<i>in the victim's death,</i>

633
00:42:56,449 --> 00:42:58,868
<i>was not carried out with any intent</i>

634
00:42:58,951 --> 00:43:02,789
<i>but instead occurred</i>
<i>under unforeseeable circumstances.</i>

635
00:43:02,872 --> 00:43:04,248
Therefore,

636
00:43:04,332 --> 00:43:06,793
this case must be assessed
in two separate parts.

637
00:43:06,876 --> 00:43:08,920
The first act
should be treated as assault,

638
00:43:09,003 --> 00:43:13,758
and the second falls under
the charge of death by traffic accident.

639
00:43:13,841 --> 00:43:14,967
I understand.

640
00:43:15,051 --> 00:43:16,135
Hyo-min is a genius.

641
