854
00:54:49,745 --> 00:54:53,540
COURT

855
00:54:53,824 --> 00:54:55,322
FINAL HEARING FOR THE MURDER CHARGE

856
00:54:55,464 --> 00:54:58,921
Your Honor, the defendant struck
the victim's head with a blunt weapon,

857
00:54:59,004 --> 00:55:02,132
which constituted the initial act
that placed the victim in mortal danger.

858
00:55:02,216 --> 00:55:03,717
The Supreme Court has set the precedent

859
00:55:03,801 --> 00:55:06,386
that when a victim who has been beaten
and mistakenly presumed dead

860
00:55:06,470 --> 00:55:08,263
dies from suffocation
after being buried alive,

861
00:55:08,347 --> 00:55:12,017
the entire course of action
amounts to one continuous act of homicide.

862
00:55:15,145 --> 00:55:19,483
The precedent cited by the prosecution
is not materially applicable to this case.

863
00:55:20,108 --> 00:55:23,111
In the precedent case,
the defendant mistakenly believed

864
00:55:23,195 --> 00:55:25,072
the victim had died
and proceeded to bury them,

865
00:55:25,155 --> 00:55:27,741
and that act was
the direct cause of death.

866
00:55:27,825 --> 00:55:29,493
However, in the current case,

867
00:55:29,576 --> 00:55:32,621
there was a separate and independent
intervention by the victim.

868
00:55:32,704 --> 00:55:36,708
This breaks the continuity
of the acts as claimed by the prosecutor.

869
00:55:37,417 --> 00:55:39,211
What exactly do you mean by

870
00:55:39,294 --> 00:55:41,046
“independent intervention?"

871
00:55:41,672 --> 00:55:45,217
It refers to the victim's
habitual jaywalking.

872
00:55:47,970 --> 00:55:52,391
The victim, Choi So-yun,
frequently violated traffic regulations.

873
00:55:52,474 --> 00:55:56,603
Three months before her death,
she was hit by a car while jaywalking

874
00:55:56,687 --> 00:55:58,355
and received outpatient treatment.

875
00:55:58,438 --> 00:56:02,317
She also had 12 traffic violations
on record over the past three years.

876
00:56:03,026 --> 00:56:04,319
And, above all…

877
00:56:11,368 --> 00:56:13,704
I SENT YOU SOME REFERENCE MATERIALS
HAVE A LOOK

878
00:56:16,248 --> 00:56:19,251
<i>In the upcoming trial,</i>
<i>the prosecutor will likely assert</i>

879
00:56:19,334 --> 00:56:22,337
<i>that the blunt force attack</i>

880
00:56:22,421 --> 00:56:25,632
<i>and the vehicle impact constitute</i>
<i>one continuous course of conduct.</i>

881
00:56:25,716 --> 00:56:27,384
<i>To refute this,</i>

882
00:56:27,467 --> 00:56:29,720
<i>it must be proven that the causal link</i>

883
00:56:29,803 --> 00:56:32,014
<i>between the act and the death was broken.</i>

884
00:56:32,097 --> 00:56:37,102
<i>You need to prove an independent break</i>
<i>in the chain of causation</i>

885
00:56:37,185 --> 00:56:39,855
<i>to disprove the prosecutor's case.</i>

886
00:56:40,480 --> 00:56:44,067
<i>I almost hit Choi So-yun with my car</i>
<i>when she was in high school.</i>

887
00:56:45,027 --> 00:56:48,322
<i>I was driving through a green light</i>

888
00:56:48,405 --> 00:56:51,533
<i>when Choi So-yun suddenly</i>
<i>walked into the middle of the street.</i>

889
00:56:52,492 --> 00:56:54,578
<i>It was a four-lane street,</i>

890
00:56:54,661 --> 00:56:57,247
<i>so it was extremely dangerous</i>
<i>for a pedestrian to cross.</i>

891
00:56:57,956 --> 00:56:59,791
<i>There was an overpass and an underpass,</i>

892
00:56:59,875 --> 00:57:02,210
<i>but Choi So-yun opted to jaywalk.</i>

893
00:57:02,878 --> 00:57:05,005
<i>People don't change easily.</i>

894
00:57:06,715 --> 00:57:07,883
This is it.

895
00:57:10,552 --> 00:57:11,511
Can you help me?

896
00:57:13,388 --> 00:57:16,350
First, we need to get the security footage
from the accident site.

897
00:57:16,433 --> 00:57:18,435
Maybe going back about six months?

898
00:57:18,518 --> 00:57:20,646
I need to request
the preservation of evidence first.

899
00:57:21,647 --> 00:57:24,191
I'll also need
the victim's traffic violation records.

900
00:57:25,567 --> 00:57:28,362
The assault took place near a bar

901
00:57:28,445 --> 00:57:30,530
frequently visited by the victim.

902
00:57:30,614 --> 00:57:34,242
The parking lot for that bar is situated
on the opposite side of the street.

903
00:57:36,578 --> 00:57:38,830
The accident occurred
on a six-lane, two-way street

904
00:57:38,914 --> 00:57:41,708
that was unsafe for pedestrians to cross,

905
00:57:41,792 --> 00:57:44,461
yet the victim chose to jaywalk.

906
00:57:45,337 --> 00:57:48,006
Moreover, during the six months prior
to her death,

907
00:57:48,090 --> 00:57:51,343
the victim visited the bar 34 times

908
00:57:51,426 --> 00:57:55,430
and crossed the road illegally
in the same manner on each occasion.

909
00:57:56,556 --> 00:57:58,892
Autopsy findings indicated that the trauma

910
00:57:58,976 --> 00:58:01,728
from the blunt weapon led
to a non-lethal concussion,

911
00:58:01,812 --> 00:58:04,106
while the actual cause of death
was a cardiac rupture

912
00:58:04,189 --> 00:58:07,275
caused by chest compression
from the vehicle collision.

913
00:58:07,359 --> 00:58:10,654
Are you saying my daughter is to blame

914
00:58:10,737 --> 00:58:12,072
for her own death?

915
00:58:14,074 --> 00:58:16,243
Do you think it makes sense?

916
00:58:17,244 --> 00:58:18,370
Order in my court!

917
00:58:18,996 --> 00:58:21,957
One more outburst,
and you will be removed from this court.

918
00:58:22,040 --> 00:58:23,000
I can't--

919
00:58:23,083 --> 00:58:24,793
Myeong-suk, no.

920
00:58:24,876 --> 00:58:26,586
Calm down.

921
00:58:26,670 --> 00:58:27,629
Calm down.

922
00:58:28,964 --> 00:58:30,173
You have to calm down.

923
00:58:32,801 --> 00:58:34,594
To accept the prosecution's claim

924
00:58:34,678 --> 00:58:37,806
is to stretch the causal link
between the defendant's actions

925
00:58:37,889 --> 00:58:40,809
and the victim's death
beyond reasonable bounds.

926
00:58:40,892 --> 00:58:42,686
This case should not be treated as murder

927
00:58:42,769 --> 00:58:46,356
but as two distinct
and independent events.

928
00:58:46,440 --> 00:58:49,860
Injury caused by a blunt object
and death caused by a vehicle collision.

929
00:58:50,652 --> 00:58:53,530
I will submit evidence
to support this claim.

930
00:58:59,453 --> 00:59:01,288
Prosecutor, proceed with the sentencing.

931
