01:04:05,884 --> 01:04:08,178
must never be justified or forgiven,

1011
01:04:08,803 --> 01:04:11,473
and she must face
the punishment it rightfully deserves.

1012
01:04:11,556 --> 01:04:15,185
But if this case is concluded
solely through punishment,

1013
01:04:15,852 --> 01:04:18,313
we will have lost yet another life.

1014
01:04:19,105 --> 01:04:21,316
The law must serve not only to punish

1015
01:04:21,941 --> 01:04:23,818
but also to offer new opportunities

1016
01:04:23,902 --> 01:04:26,613
through rehabilitation
and reintegration into society.

1017
01:04:27,238 --> 01:04:29,115
The crime committed by Kim Yeong-mi

1018
01:04:29,199 --> 01:04:31,076
is not merely a personal tragedy

1019
01:04:31,159 --> 01:04:34,662
but the result of a societal failure
we chose to ignore.

1020
01:04:35,455 --> 01:04:37,332
Supporting her rehabilitation

1021
01:04:37,874 --> 01:04:40,543
is more than an act
of personal redemption.

1022
01:04:40,627 --> 01:04:42,462
It's a way
for us to restore the compassion

1023
01:04:42,545 --> 01:04:44,172
and responsibility we neglected

1024
01:04:44,255 --> 01:04:46,800
and a path toward
a more just and humane society.

1025
01:04:48,593 --> 01:04:50,011
I would like to submit a petition

1026
01:04:50,095 --> 01:04:53,473
written by 84 of the defendant's
high school classmates,

1027
01:04:53,556 --> 01:04:55,100
bystanders like myself.

1028
01:04:59,312 --> 01:05:00,522
Your Honor,

1029
01:05:00,605 --> 01:05:02,399
I earnestly ask the court
to carefully consider

1030
01:05:02,482 --> 01:05:05,318
these materials and the petition

1031
01:05:05,402 --> 01:05:07,320
in determining the appropriate sentence.

1032
01:05:07,946 --> 01:05:11,491
Please allow Kim Yeong-mi the opportunity

1033
01:05:11,574 --> 01:05:13,368
to start over and rebuild her life.

1034
01:05:16,371 --> 01:05:17,622
Defendant.

1035
01:05:20,333 --> 01:05:22,085
You may make your final statement.

1036
01:05:31,302 --> 01:05:32,595
I admit my wrongdoing.

1037
01:05:34,055 --> 01:05:36,724
I truly regret my actions.

1038
01:05:38,560 --> 01:05:42,105
I will humbly accept
the sentence I am given.

1039
01:06:02,208 --> 01:06:04,544
The court will now deliver its verdict.

1040
01:06:06,379 --> 01:06:07,922
The court

1041
01:06:08,006 --> 01:06:11,050
finds merit in the defense's claim
that there is a break

1042
01:06:11,134 --> 01:06:13,303
in the chain of causation

1043
01:06:13,928 --> 01:06:17,599
between the defendant's assault
with a blunt weapon

1044
01:06:18,099 --> 01:06:19,434
and the victim's death.

1045
01:06:19,976 --> 01:06:23,354
As such, the act of assault
and the vehicle collision are determined

1046
01:06:23,897 --> 01:06:25,773
to be unrelated and separate occurrences.

1047
01:06:26,733 --> 01:06:27,859
First,

1048
01:06:28,443 --> 01:06:29,611
the defendant

1049
01:06:29,694 --> 01:06:33,364
struck the victim with a blunt object
with the intent to cause bodily harm,

1050
01:06:33,448 --> 01:06:35,492
resulting in a concussion.

1051
01:06:36,242 --> 01:06:39,704
Accordingly, the elements of the crime
of bodily injury are satisfied.

1052
01:06:39,787 --> 01:06:42,832
Second, with regard
to the vehicle accident,

1053
01:06:42,916 --> 01:06:46,503
the defendant failed
to properly maintain a lookout ahead,

1054
01:06:47,003 --> 01:06:50,423
resulting in the victim's death.
This constitutes a charge of causing death

1055
01:06:50,507 --> 01:06:55,428
under the Special Act
on Traffic Accident Settlement.

1056
01:06:56,346 --> 01:06:59,432
For the two offenses, the court
hereby sentences the defendant

1057
01:07:00,308 --> 01:07:02,769
to two years of imprisonment.

1058
01:07:05,104 --> 01:07:07,565
That concludes the court's ruling.

1059
01:08:02,078 --> 01:08:03,413
<i>What's all this?</i>

1060
01:08:04,038 --> 01:08:07,125
The bullying videos and photos found
on Choi So-yun's phone.

1061
01:08:07,208 --> 01:08:10,044
You still had her phone?

1062
01:08:10,128 --> 01:08:11,129
Yes.

1063
01:08:13,256 --> 01:08:16,134
I never ended up giving it back to her.

1064
01:08:16,217 --> 01:08:17,510
It was in storage.

1065
01:08:18,261 --> 01:08:20,138
This will help with the sentencing.

1066
01:08:22,765 --> 01:08:24,726
About what you said earlier…

1067
01:08:25,768 --> 01:08:27,186
Mom, I was--

1068
01:08:27,270 --> 01:08:30,773
If I could go back in time
with my current age, experience,

1069
01:08:30,857 --> 01:08:33,860
and everything I've learned,

1070
01:08:33,943 --> 01:08:36,112
I might make a wiser choice.

1071
01:08:37,822 --> 01:08:39,157
But

1072
01:08:40,116 --> 01:08:43,036
it was the best decision
I could make at that time,

1073
01:08:43,620 --> 01:08:45,413
and I can't change that now.

1074
01:08:47,415 --> 01:08:48,291
Because

1075
01:08:49,959 --> 01:08:51,961
at the heart of every decision I made

1076
01:08:52,879 --> 01:08:57,300
was my love for you, Hyo-min.

1077
01:08:58,968 --> 01:09:00,970
As long as that love remains unchanged,

1078
01:09:02,180 --> 01:09:06,476
I would make the same decision every time,
even if I could go back to the past.

1079
01:09:06,559 --> 01:09:08,895
That's why I said
I don't regret my decisions.

1080
01:09:09,729 --> 01:09:10,938
But…

1081
01:09:13,733 --> 01:09:15,109
having heard what you said,

1082
01:09:16,986 --> 01:09:18,696
I feel regret for the first time.

1083
01:09:42,595 --> 01:09:44,847
<i>I can take care of it.</i>
<i>Why are you butting in?</i>

1084
01:09:52,397 --> 01:09:53,981
- What are you doing?
- Oh, gosh.

1085
01:09:55,650 --> 01:09:56,943
Mr. Yoon.

1086
01:09:58,486 --> 01:10:00,780
I thought you guys
were having a get-together.

1087
01:10:00,863 --> 01:10:03,116
Everyone is
at the fried chicken spot nearby.

1088
01:10:05,034 --> 01:10:06,202
Is something wrong?

1089
01:10:12,250 --> 01:10:13,126
It's just…

1090
01:10:14,168 --> 01:10:15,920
My head feels a bit heavy.

1091
01:10:19,132 --> 01:10:21,300
Why are you still here?

1092
01:10:21,384 --> 01:10:22,802
I have some work left.

1093
01:10:23,803 --> 01:10:26,013
I sometimes come up here to clear my head.

1094
01:10:27,974 --> 01:10:28,933
It's nice.

1095
01:10:29,559 --> 01:10:30,435
What is?

1096
01:10:31,102 --> 01:10:32,395
Just everything.

1097
01:10:32,478 --> 01:10:34,814
The view, the vibe,

1098
01:10:34,897 --> 01:10:36,065
and

1099
01:10:37,275 --> 01:10:39,902
my unexpected encounter with you.

1100
01:10:40,445 --> 01:10:41,571
Everything.

1101
01:10:45,908 --> 01:10:47,034
Today's trial…

1102
01:10:49,078 --> 01:10:51,831
was one of the most impressive
I've ever seen.

1103
01:10:53,249 --> 01:10:54,167
Really?

1104
01:10:57,378 --> 01:11:01,632
They say people make
intuitive judgments first

1105
01:11:01,716 --> 01:11:04,302
and then come up
with logical reasons afterward.

1106
01:11:04,385 --> 01:11:06,471
That's why they say
intuition is a gift from God,

1107
01:11:06,554 --> 01:11:09,307
and reason is its faithful servant.

1108
01:11:09,932 --> 01:11:13,102
Your argument was both intuitive
and technically well-supported,

1109
01:11:13,186 --> 01:11:16,773
presenting clear logical reasoning
to the judge.

1110
01:11:17,482 --> 01:11:20,485
It also maintained a good balance
between emotion and reason.

1111
01:11:20,568 --> 01:11:21,444
You did well.

1112
01:11:23,404 --> 01:11:25,364
You did well too.

1113
01:11:27,241 --> 01:11:28,576
What did I do well?

1114
01:11:30,453 --> 01:11:33,873
When you meet a client wanting
to heal their scars through a lawsuit,

1115
01:11:34,373 --> 01:11:35,792
you need to look beneath the scars.

1116
01:11:39,629 --> 01:11:42,298
Let go of your biases
and look at the essence.

1117
01:11:43,508 --> 01:11:45,134
To me,

1118
01:11:45,218 --> 01:11:47,553
justice means protecting the people
I have to protect.

1119
01:11:48,513 --> 01:11:50,973
Don't think like a small mind
trapped in dogma.

1120
01:11:51,766 --> 01:11:52,934
Try to see the bigger picture.

1121
01:11:53,017 --> 01:11:56,395
You're an awesome sculptor.

1122
01:11:56,938 --> 01:11:59,482
You patiently chip away at the rough edges

1123
01:11:59,565 --> 01:12:01,234
and shortcomings of the associates

1124
01:12:01,859 --> 01:12:04,737
and bring out potential
they didn't even know they had.

1125
01:12:06,072 --> 01:12:10,910
Of all your sculptures,
who is your greatest masterpiece?

1126
01:12:12,662 --> 01:12:13,913
Lee Jin-woo?

1127
01:12:16,707 --> 01:12:17,625
Kang Hyo-min?

1128
01:12:22,839 --> 01:12:24,340
You should smile more often.

1129
01:12:24,423 --> 01:12:25,925
There's no reason to hide your smile.

1130
01:12:26,008 --> 01:12:27,677
I will.

1131
01:13:34,535 --> 01:13:37,413
BEYOND THE BAR

1132
01:13:37,496 --> 01:13:38,581
<i>What are you gonna do?</i>

1133
01:13:38,664 --> 01:13:41,083
<i>Let's begin by taking all actions</i>
<i>permitted under existing law.</i>

1134
01:13:41,192 --> 01:13:42,923
<i>- What's your deal, you bastard?</i>
<i>- Mr. Yoon.</i>

1135
01:13:43,753 --> 01:13:45,379
Mr. Yoon, pull yourself together.

1136
01:13:46,923 --> 01:13:48,215
I'm counting on you.

1137
01:13:48,299 --> 01:13:49,383
I'm so worried about him.

1138
01:13:49,467 --> 01:13:52,219
<i>- You still should've told me.</i>
<i>- Did you ever give me a chance?</i>

1139
01:13:52,303 --> 01:13:54,138
You should've made me understand you.

1140
01:13:54,221 --> 01:13:56,307
I was wondering if you had plans tomorrow.

1141
01:13:56,390 --> 01:13:57,808
<i>- Hello.</i>
<i>- Let's go.</i>

1142
01:13:57,892 --> 01:14:01,187
<i>Mr. Ha Du-sik is backed</i>
<i>by Mr. Ko Seung-cheol.</i>

1143
01:14:01,270 --> 01:14:02,563
<i>He won't just stand by and watch.</i>

1144
01:14:02,647 --> 01:14:04,440
<i>They've filed a lawsuit</i>
<i>against Bluestone Fund.</i>

1145
01:14:04,523 --> 01:14:06,192
You'll get your company back.

1146
